    .docs-content
      h1 Action Sheet React Component
      p Action Sheet is a slide-up pane for presenting the user with a set of alternatives for how to proceed with a given task. You can also use action sheets to prompt the user to confirm a potentially dangerous action. The action sheet contains an optional title and one or more buttons, each of which corresponds to an action to take.
      p Action Sheet React component represents <a href="../docs/action-sheet.html">Action Sheet</a> component.
      h2 Usage example
      pre
        code
          :code
            <!-- Actions -->
            <Actions>
              <!-- Actions Group -->
              <ActionsGroup>
                <!-- Actions Label -->
                <ActionsLabel>Hello</ActionsLabel>
                <!-- Actions Buttons -->
                <ActionsButton>Button 1</ActionsButton>
                <ActionsButton onClick={doSomething}>Button 2</ActionsButton>
              </ActionsGroup>
              <!-- Another Group -->
              <ActionsGroup>
                <!-- Cancel/Close Button -->
                <ActionsButton color="red" bold>Cancel</ActionsButton>
              </ActionsGroup>
            </Actions>
      p Renders to:
      pre
        code
          :code
            <div class="actions-modal">
              <div class="actions-modal-group">
                <div class="actions-modal-label">Hello</div>
                <div class="actions-modal-button">Button 1</div>
                <div class="actions-modal-button">Button 2</div>
              </div>
              <div class="actions-modal-group">
                <div class="actions-modal-button color-red actions-modal-button-bold">Cancel</div>
              </div>
            </div>
